
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Cervid · Radical Infrastructure for Node.js</title>
    <meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy" content="upgrade-insecure-requests">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;700;900&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles/main.css">
</head>
<body>

<nav>
    <a href="/" class="nav-logo">
        <svg class="logo-img" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" width="35" height="35">
            <path d="M12 2L4.5 20.29L5.21 21L12 18L18.79 21L19.5 20.29L12 2Z" fill="var(--accent)"/>
        </svg>
        <div class="logo-name">
            <span class="logo-text-cerv">CERV</span><span class="logo-text-id">ID</span>
        </div>
    </a>
<div class="nav-right">
    <a href="https://github.com/cervid-io" class="nav-link">GITHUB</a>
</div>
</nav>

<header class="mother-hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
        <h1 class="hero-title">
            <span class="line-1">RADICAL</span>
            <span class="line-2">INFRASTRUCTURE</span>
            <span class="line-3">FOR NODE.JS</span>
        </h1>
     <p class="hero-tagline">
        Zero-dependency, high-performance tools designed to push JavaScript beyond its limits. Built for the next generation of data-intensive applications.
    </p>
    </div>
</header>

<main class="ecosystem-grid">
    <a href="/data" class="card live">
        <div class="card-status">v1.0.0 // LIVE</div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="card-title">@cervid/data</h2>
            <p class="card-text">Ultra-fast columnar engine. Leveraging Shared Memory and Worker Threads for native processing speed.</p>
            <div class="card-tags">
                <span>Columnar</span><span>SIMD</span><span>Workers</span><span>CSV</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </a>

    <a class="card blueprint">
        <div class="card-status">IN CONSTRUCTION // PROTOTYPE</div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="card-title">@cervid/decomposer</h2>
            <p class="card-text">Binary format deconstruction. Pure Node.js reader for Parquet, Arrow, and Avro files.</p>
            <div class="card-tags">
                <span>Binary</span><span>Parquet</span><span>IPC</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </a>
</main>

<section class="roadmap">
    <div class="roadmap-title">> CERVID_PROJECT_MANIFESTO</div>
    <div class="roadmap-list">
        <div class="roadmap-group">
            <span class="roadmap-year">2026 Q3-Q4</span>
            <div class="roadmap-item">
                <span class="roadmap-connector">└─</span>
                <span class="roadmap-name">@cervid/vision</span>
                <span class="roadmap-comment">← image processing & computer vision</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="philosophy">
    <div class="philosophy-item">
        <h3>01 // NATIVE CORE</h3>
        <p>No native modules required. We leverage the power of modern V8 features like SharedArrayBuffers and BigInt for maximum portability.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="philosophy-item">
        <h3>02 // ZERO OVERHEAD</h3>
        <p>Built for production. We focus on memory efficiency and zero-copy data operations to minimize the impact on the Garbage Collector.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="philosophy-item">
        <h3>03 // SCALE FIRST</h3>
        <p>Designed to handle millions of rows in milliseconds. Every library in the Cervid family is tested against massive real-world datasets.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<footer>
    <div class="footer-brand">CERVID.IO</div>
    <div class="footer-copy">© 2026 ALBETRAN TECHNOLOGIES. POWERED BY PURE NODE.JS CORE.</div>
</footer>

</body>
</html>